Kenya’s general management of the coronavirus pandemic leaves a lot to be desired. For Nairobi to throw a tantrum at the UK for taking precautions to protect its citizens is to bury its head in the sand. The law change drive is facing a timeline nightmare even as Parliament goes on a one-month recess. The government’s appetite for debt shot up by 69 per cent between March 2020 and March 2021. Senator is touring counties, holding strategy meetings with advisers and regional leaders.